 ø  Overview


    Tables consists of rows (records) of data

    Rows consists of variables (fields) of data

    _____________Ö_____________________Ö___________________________^
                 ×  &NAME              ×  &ADDRESS                 ×
    _____________+_____________________+___________________________@
    Row number 1 ×  Bob Zimmerman      ×  1234 State Street        ×
    _____________+_____________________+___________________________@
    Row number 2 ×  Bruce Lomar        ×  1236 Wabash Street       ×
    _____________$_____________________$___________________________<



 ø  ISPF Table Services


    ô  Creates a table

    ô  Opens a table previously closed

    ô  Saves a table (permanent tables)

    ô  Closes a table with or without saving it

    ô  Deletes tables
1Introduction to Dialog Manager                                      Pag



       _________________________________________________________________
       ×
       ×
       ×                    ISPF Tables (continued)
       ×
       ×________________________________________________________________




 ø  ISPF Tables Services for rows of the table


    ô  A row can have unlimited amount of variables (fields)

    ô  The data the row represents is limited to 32k

    ô  Pointing to row "x" will fill the variables of the table with the
       data of that row.

    ô  Any single row can be "extended" with extra variables pertinent t
       that row.



    ø  ISPF Tables Services for columns of a table


       ô  You may scan a table for a specific value(s) in a given
       variable(s).



 ø  Temporary tables  vs.  Permanent Tables

    Permanent tables are saved on DISK (ISPTABL) and may be opened from
    (ISPTLIB).

    Temporary tables exist only in storage and are deleted from storage.

    Permanent tables may be shared across users (for read only).
1Introduction to Dialog Manager                                      Pag



    ____________________________________________________________________
    ×
    ×
    ×                      ISPF Tables (continued)
    ×
    ×___________________________________________________________________




 ø  Keyed  vs.  non-Keyed tables

    Any row variable(s) can be designated as the key to the table.

    Duplicate keys are not allowed.

    In ISPF RELEASE 2, keyed tables are maintained in key sequence.

    Rows of a keyed table may be accessed directly by a key.



 ø  Displaying the data of a table

    Any single row can be displayed/updated by a data entry panel.

    Display of 2 or more rows requires a special TABLE DISPLAY panel.

    On the Table Display panel, you may select which variables of the ro
    should be displayed.

    Table Display panels do not support )PROC section.
    This is only Release 1.
    This only applies to the table variables.

    The display is maintained by ISPF (Scrollable).
1Introduction to Dialog Manager                                      Pag



    ____________________________________________________________________
    ×
    ×
    ×                      ISPF Tables (continued)
    ×
    ×___________________________________________________________________




 ø  LIMITATIONS

    There is no SORT Facility in release 1 to SORT the tables.

    Permanent tables should be limited in size because of overhead.
